<paragraph blockId="36.[826,1441,476,590]" pageId="36" pageNumber="258">
<emphasis box="[826,952,476,497]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="258">Etymology:</emphasis>
Derived from the Latin ‘amplius’ meaning ‘larger’. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Davis &amp; Gentili-Poole &amp; Mitter" authorityYear="2008" box="[928,1273,506,527]" class="Insecta" family="Cossidae" genus="Simplicivalva" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="258" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ampliophilobia">
<emphasis box="[928,1273,506,527]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="258">Simplicivalva ampliophilobia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
refers to the larger size of this species as compared with the very similar, smaller species 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Druce" authorityYear="1898" box="[1108,1235,568,589]" class="Insecta" family="Cossidae" genus="Arbela" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="258" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="philobia">
<emphasis box="[1108,1235,568,589]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="258">S. philobia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="36.[826,1441,630,835]" pageId="36" pageNumber="258">
<emphasis box="[826,954,630,651]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="258">Discussion:</emphasis>
This species most closely resembles two species not known to occur in 
<collectingCountry box="[1164,1288,660,682]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="36" pageNumber="258">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Davis &amp; Gentili-Poole &amp; Mitter" authorityYear="2008" baseAuthorityName="Clench" baseAuthorityYear="1961" box="[1298,1391,660,682]" class="Insecta" family="Cossidae" genus="Simplicivalva" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="258" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eberti">
<emphasis box="[1298,1391,660,682]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="258">S. eberti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Druce" authorityYear="1898" box="[826,951,691,712]" class="Insecta" family="Cossidae" genus="Arbela" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="258" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="philobia">
<emphasis box="[826,951,691,712]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="258">S. philobia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1019,1092,691,713]" name="Brazil" pageId="36" pageNumber="258">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. 
